OPERATION FIELA II has resulted in 1238 people between ages
of 19 and 68 being arrested, for various crimes over the weekend. Their crimes range from murder, attempted murder, rape,
armed robbery, burglary residence, business robbery, business burglary, escape
from lawful custody, and theft of motor vehicle. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said an intelligent
led operation led to the suspects who had fraudulent identity documents and
were signatories of business bank accounts with millions of Rands. “They were arrested during a transaction in progress inside
the bank and their Polo GTI was also confiscated,” Ngoepe said. 